1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. c3 Nf6 5. d4
{ This move is still often played nowadays, so it is essential for Black to know it well. }
5... exd4 6. e5 d5 7. exf6
{ This looks dangerous, but it is actually wrong, as we will see. } 7... dxc4
8. fxg7 Rg8 9. O-O Qf6
{ Black will capture on g7, with some powerful threats against White's castle, and play ...Be6 next, followed by ...O-O-O with an awesome position. }
