[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter"]
[Black "Italian, Main lines #3"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. c3 Nf6 5. d3 d6 6. O-O a5
{ Stopping White's b4-expansion and freeing the a7-square for the bishop to stay out of harm's way. }
7. Re1 O-O
{ White's plan is regrouping the b1-knight to g3 and try to push d4. This may or may not include playing h3. }
8. h3 Ba7 { Again saving the bishop before the d4 push comes. } 9. Nbd2 Be6 10.
Bb5
{ After  10.Bxe6  fxe6  11.Nf1  we would end up reachingthe same line we have examined under 8.Nbd2. }
10... Ne7
{ Once again, the knight is heading to g6 allowing White to push d4, but setting up a central and kingside attack. }
11. d4 Ng6
{ White has several options now, but Black will always find a plan in the center or kingside. }
12. Bd3 { Overprotecting e4. Usually c2 is a good square for this bishop. }
12... Nh5
{ Aiming at the outpost on f4. White can never play g3, as that would leave h3 unprotected, so there is no easy way to expel that knight. }
13. Bc2
{ The knight on f4 would hit the bishop on d3, so it has to be removed. The typical idea  13.Nxe5  intending Qxh5 loses easily to  13...Ngf4  . }
13... Nhf4 14. Nf1 Qd7
{ Black's attack starts to show. Moves like Nxg2 or Bxh3 are already very interesting, to rip White's castle open. }
15. Ne3
{ Not the ideal square for this knight, blocking the c1-bishop, but here it protects g2, which was necessary in some lines like  15.dxe5  Nxg2  with a winning attack. }
15... exd4
{ The knight on f4 is still covering the d5-square, so Black can afford this central break. }
16. Nxd4 Bxd4 17. cxd4
{ 17.Qxd4  looks normal, but the queen is not protecting the light squares anymore, and  17...Rae8  with the idea of Nh4 or even Bxh3 in some scenarios is a very strong reply, giving Black a clear edge. }
17... d5 18. e5
{ Again this natural move is the worst choice, but any other move would allow Black to achieve their goals: an isolated pawn on d4 and a good blockade on the d5-square. }
18... Nh4
{ Black's attack is winning. The main threat is simply ...f6 and once the f-file is open for the rook, potential sacrifices on h3 and g2 will be lethal. }
