Be6 9. Be3 Be7 10. c3 O-O 11. Nbd2
{ Here we reach the typical position of this line with 9.Be3. Black has several alternatives and here I will analyze only 11...Qd7 because I like the resulting type of position, but both  11...Bg4  and  11...Nxd2  are playable as well. }
11... Qd7 12. Re1 Nxd2 13. Qxd2 Na5
{ Besides improving the knight, Black makes way for the ...c5 push, intending to control the important d4-square. }
