1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6
{ 5.Nc3  would transpose to theFour Knights. } 5... bxc6 6. e5
{ The main move. } 6... Qe7 7. Qe2 Nd5 8. h4
{ This move has recently become very popular and we should be ready to face it. }
8... Qe6
{ Black prepares to develop their bishop and castle.  8...d6  is also possible. }
9. g3 { Intending Bh3. } 9... d6 10. c4
{ After  10.exd6  Bxd6  , our development lead offers more than enough compensation for our crippled structure. }
10... Nb6 11. exd6
{ This move was played by Nepomniachtchi against Kramnik, but does not look good.  11.Bf4  dxe5  12.Qxe5  Bb4⩲  and next Black will castle with a drawish position. }
11... Bxd6 12. Be3 O-O 13. Nd2 Re8
{ Black is clearly better, as we are currently threatening ...Bxg3 followed by ...Qxe3. }
