1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6
{ 5.Nc3  would transpose to theFour Knights. } 5... bxc6 6. e5
{ The main move. } 6... Qe7 7. Qe2 Nd5 8. h4
{ This move has recently become very popular and we should be ready to face it. }
8... Qe6
{ Black prepares to develop their bishop and castle.  8...d6  is also possible. }
9. Nd2 a5
{ A very useful move that has lots of merits. First, it allows Ba6 and secures the b4-square for the knight or the bishop. As White's plan usually involves a c4 + b3 pawn formation, a potential a4 push may be quite challenging to face. }
10. Nf3 Bc5
{ Now it is a good time to develop our bishop, as White cannot hit it with their knight. Black simply wants to castle. }
11. c4 Nb6 12. Qc2 Qg6
{ 12...O-O  was not good because of  13.Bd3  . Once this idea is averted, Black is ready to castle and break the center with ...d6. }
*

