{ The two main moves here are by far  4.d4  and  4.Bb5  . The most played alternatives are  4.Bc4  , which we will examine in the Italian section, and  4.g3  , which will be briefly covered here. I will show you a simple plan for Black. }
4. Bb5 Bb4 { 4...Nd4  is the other fine alternative. } 5. O-O O-O 6. d3 d6
{ So far, standard piece development for both sides. Now there are two possible approaches for White. }
7. Ne2
{ The most solid. White intends to transfer the knight to g3, playing for c3 and d4 as in the Italian. }
7... Ne7 { Black follows suit. } 8. c3 Ba5 9. Ng3 c6 10. Ba4 Ng6 11. d4
{ White gets their d4 push first but, as we will see, White's center is shakier than it looks. If  11.h3  Black can play  11...d5  . }
