1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6
{ The two main moves here are by far  4.d4  and  4.Bb5  . The most played alternatives are  4.Bc4  , which we will examine in the Italian section, and  4.g3  , which will be briefly covered here. I will show you a simple plan for Black. }
4. d4 exd4 5. Nxd4 Bb4 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. Bd3
{ 7.e5  is not so good due to  7...Qe7  . } 7... O-O 8. O-O d5 9. exd5
{ 9.e5  was not so good due to  9...Ng4  . } 9... cxd5 10. h3
{ The best try in this position. I have played this from both sides and I think it is equal. However, this plan is worth knowing with Black. }
