[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. b4
{ The Evans Gambit! Not a usual sight nowadays, but good to know how to handle it. }
4... Bxb4 5. c3 Be7
{ Recently, the most usual move, with good reason. Black sidesteps the sharpest lines and simply wants to return the pawn to develop quickly. }
6. d4 Na5
{ An important move, kicking the bishop away from c4. Black offers the e5-pawn to get some initiative. }
7. Bd3 d6 { Black gives the pawn back to speed development. } *

