{ This move is still often played nowadays, so it is essential for Black to know it well. }
5... exd4 6. e5 d5 7. Bb5 { The main move. } 7... Ne4 8. cxd4 Bb6 9. Nc3 O-O
10. O-O
{ This move is not often played. A better option is overprotecting the d4-pawn with  10.Be3  . }
10... Bg4 11. Be3 f6 12. exf6 Nxf6
{ In comparison with other lines, the difference here is that White had skipped h3 and now this move would come too late, as d4 is dropping; therefore, I think the h3-g4 idea is not possible. }
13. Be2 Qd6
{ Being forced to bring the bishop back to e2 is a clear sign that something has gone wrong for White. Black is very fine. }
