10. Be3 { It is important for White to keep the d4-pawn well protected. } 10...
Bg4 { Pinning the f3-knight, in charge of the defense of d4 and e5. } 11. h3
Bh5
{ Now  12.Qc2  is by far the most played move, but I will examine some alternatives. Despite not being so popular, these moves are interesting as well and worth knowing. }
12. Qc2 Ba5
{ This move has recently become very popular. Black pins the c3-knight and forces matters. }
13. O-O Bxf3 14. gxf3 Nxd4
{ Black sacrifices the knight to deflect the e3-bishop. The black queen joins the attack and will seek a perpetual. }
15. Bxd4 Qg5+ 16. Kh1
