[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Italian with 5.Nc3"]
[Black "Italian, 5.Nc3 h6 6.h3 a6"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. d3 Nf6 5. Nc3
{ This move is not too dangerous, but we need to know some ideas. } 5... h6
{ Preventing one of those ideas: Bg5 followed by Nd5. } 6. h3 a6
{ This move prevents another standard idea for White: after  6...d6  7.Na4  White wins the bishop pair and can fight for an opening advantage. }
7. a3 { 7.O-O  would transpose to our main line. } 7... d6
{ White was setting a trap: after  7...O-O  8.g4!  , White's attack is very powerful, so we wait for White to castle kingside before castling ourselves. }
8. Ba2
{ After  8.O-O  Black can play either  8...O-O  or  8...g5!?  with the same attacking idea. }
8... Be6
{ Once all White's plans have been prevented, Black has no problem at all. } *

[Event "?"]
