[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. d3 Nf6 5. Nc3
{ This move is not too dangerous, but we need to know some ideas. } 5... h6
{ Preventing one of those ideas: Bg5 followed by Nd5. } 6. O-O O-O 7. Be3 Bb6
{ 7...Bxe3  is also playable, but in this position Black needs to be somewhat careful, as the f-file is open. After  7...Bb6  Black has no worries. }
8. Qd2
{ 8.h3  d6  Again intending ...Na5.  9.a4  Be6=  This position is very balanced. }
8... d6
{ 9.Bxh6  does not work, as after all the captures on h6 Black has  10...Nh7  or  10...Ng4  . }
9. h3 { Bg4 was an annoying threat. } 9... Na5
{ Black will trade their knight for White's bishop, with a nice position. } *

