1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. d3 Nf6 5. Nc3
{ This move is not too dangerous, but we need to know some ideas. } 5... h6
{ Preventing one of those ideas: Bg5 followed by Nd5. } 6. O-O O-O 7. h3 a6
{ Once again, after  7...d6  8.Na4  White takes the black bishop. } 8. Be3 d6
{ Taking on e3 is again possible, but I prefer this waiting move.  9.Bxc5  does not trouble us, as we will see. }
9. Bxc5 dxc5 10. Bd5
{ White's only try to stop Black's stabilization. Against any other move, Black can continue by ...Qd6 followed by ...Be6 with a nice position. }
