{ 19...Bd5  is interesting too, but this move puts pressure on d4 and plans a beautiful combination. }
20. Rh4 Rxd4 { A beautiful move, forcing the perpetual. } 21. Rxd4 Bd5 22. Rxd5
{ Only move to avoid defeat. } 22... Qxg3+ { Using the pin on f2. } 23. Kh1
Qh3+ 24. Kg1 Qg3+ { With a draw by repetition. } *

