1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Bxc6
{ A rare guest in top tournaments, as practice has shown that Black is perfectly fine in this line. Still, it is important to know this type of position, where a structure with doubled c-pawns arise. }
4... dxc6 5. O-O
{ 5.Nxe5  is not possible due to  5...Qd4  and Black gets the pawn back with a better position. }
5... Qf6
