6. d4
{ White needs to play active after giving up one of their bishops for a quicker development. }
6... exd4 7. Bg5 Qd6
{ It may look like White is developing their whole army, while Black is just moving their queen around. However, Black will always have a good grip on light squares, which leaves us out of trouble. Also, Black just needs to develop the c8-bishop and will be ready to castle queenside. }
8. Nxd4 Be7 { 8...Bd7  is also a good alternative. } 9. Be3 Nf6
{ 9...Nh6  is a very interesting and aggressive option, successfully tried by Caruana, but I prefer the text, as it is simpler. }
10. f3 { 10.Nc3  was not possible due to  10...Ng4  . } 10... c5 11. Ne2
