{ This move is always important: we should not allow White getting d4 in with a tempo. }
9. Bg5
{ This move is not so logical without the bishop on the a2-g8 diagonal. } 9...
h6 10. Bh4 g5
{ 11.Bxg5  hxg5  12.Nxg5  is met by  12...Ng4  and Black is in charge. } 11.
Bg3 Ne7 12. d4 Ng6
{ Black is already better, as we are in time to defend e5 and White's bishop is pointless on g3. Taking everything on e5 is not possible due to ...Bxf2 followed by ...Ng4. }
*

