[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Spanish 5.d3 Bc5"]
[Black "Spanish, Anderssen Variation: 6.c3 d6 7.O-O O-O 8.h3 Ba7"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. d3 Bc5 6. c3
{ A natural move preparing d4.  6.O-O  d6  7.c3  O-O  Transposing to the main line. Skipping c3 makes no sense for White. }
6... d6 7. O-O O-O
{ Reaching an Italian-like position, but White's bishop stands on a4 instead of c4. Black's main idea is regrouping the knight to g6 via e7. }
8. h3 Ba7 9. Re1 h6
{ An important move.  9...Ne7  was not that good. As White has not commited their b1-knight, a possible setup is d4-Bc2-Be3 and Nbd2. }
10. Nbd2 Ne7
{ Now it is the right time for this regrouping. Again, Black's knight gets to g6 before White's reaches g3. }
11. Nf1 Ng6 12. Ng3 c5
{ This move blocks our a7-bishop, but it is fully justified, as it stops White's only break d4. }
13. Bb3
{ Stopping ...d5. If  13.Be3  or  13.Bc2  we would play  13...d5  with some good central control. }
13... Be6
{ With an equal position. White has no better plan than the d4 push, which would bring our a7-bishop back to life. And otherwise, Black can prepare their own ...d5 break. }
*

