{ Tying up the knight on f3 that is defending e5. This pawn is going to suffer a bit if White does not play precise. }
14. Qd3
{ 14.Bf4  it is possible but after  14...Bxf3  15.gxf3  Black can decide between several moves like Rad8 or Nd8 with idea of Ne6, interesting play. }
14... g6 { Avoiding mate on h7 and allowing Bf5 on some lines. } 15. Bf4 Bf5
16. Qd2 Bxc2 17. Qxc2 Nd8
{ The knight goes to e6 where will control the black squares on the kingside. White has no easy plan as black is going to put the rooks in the center and play ...c5. }
*

