{ It seems crazy but the lack of white development on the queenside, the activity of the black pieces and the control of the center makes it possible for this to work. }
13. Re2 { Probably the best option. } 13... Bf2+ 14. Rxf2 Nxf2 15. Kxf2 Re8
{ White has two pieces for rook and pawn. Normally in the middle game the two pieces are better, but in this case black is going to be strong on the e file with the major pieces which is going to give him a good game. }
16. Kg1 c5 17. Nxe6 Rxe6
{ Black's rooks have the e file to activate and White's pieces do not have good squares. }
