10. Re1 O-O 11. Nbd2 Nc5 12. Nd4
{ Now that e5 is defended this move is possible. } 12... Nxd4 13. cxd4 Nd3
{ Important to avoid  13...Nxb3  14.Nxb3  after which White would have a good control of the c5 break. }
14. Re3 Nxc1 15. Rxc1 a5
{ Black gains space on the queenside and disturbs the bishop on b3 before preparing the c5-break. }
16. Rec3 Rc8
{ White seems to press hard on the c file and prevent c5 for the moment, but Black has good resources and is going to end up making the break sooner or later. }
