10. Bf4 { The idea is to defend e5 in order to be able to play Nd4. } 10... Nc5
{ Getting ahead of the white idea. } 11. Nd4 Nxd4 12. cxd4 Nxb3 13. Qxb3
{ White would only be fine in this position if he had control of the c5-break, but he does not. }
13... h5
{ This interesting idea I employed against Adhiban and it guards a little trap he fell into. }
14. Nd2 c5
{ This is the idea. Now White cannot capture on c5 by the move g5 winning the bishop. }
15. Rfc1 c4
{ Black has an ideal position with the pawn on c4 and the bishop pair and I ended up winning in Adhiban-Anton. }
