1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Nxe4 6. d4 b5 7. Bb3 d5 8. dxe5
Be6 9. Nbd2 Be7 10. c3 O-O 11. Bc2 f5 12. Nb3
{ The main line. White aims to get a knight into d4 by knocking on e6 and c6. }
12... Qd7 { Defending c6 and e6 and connecting rooks. } 13. Re1 Rad8 14. Nfd4
{ After  14.Nbd4  Nxd4  , Black would get a better version of the main line. }
14... Nxe5
{ After  14...Nxd4  15.cxd4  Black no longer has the move a5 and White has good control of c5 and threatens f3. }
15. f3 Bf7 16. fxe4 fxe4
{ This piece sacrifice is thematic in this line. Black gets two central pawns for the piece and has great initiative on the center and kingside while the white pieces are dominated by the black pawns. }
