14... c5 15. Ne2 Rad8 { Black keeps putting more pieces in the center. } 16. f3
Ng5 17. Be3 d4
{ Other moves are also interesting, but this is the most straightforward and works because of the d file control. }
18. cxd4 Bc4
{ Pinning the knight on e2 which controls d4 and giving the e6 square to the knight on g5. }
19. b3 Bxe2 20. Qxe2 cxd4 21. Rad1 Ne6 22. Bc1 Nc5 23. Bd3 f4
{ Black can exchange on d3 and occupy the f5 square. } *

