[Black "Open Spanish Open with 12.Nb3 13.Nfd4 #6"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Nxe4 6. d4 b5 7. Bb3 d5 8. dxe5
Be6 9. Nbd2 Be7 10. c3 O-O 11. Bc2 f5 12. Nb3
{ The main line. White aims to get a knight into d4 by knocking on e6 and c6. }
12... Qd7 { Defending c6 and e6 and connecting rooks. } 13. Nfd4
{ 13.Nbd4  it is played more but after  13...Nxd4  14.Nxd4  it transposes to the main line and also gives an extra option to Black:  13...Nd8!?  , so more and more people are going for this move. }
13... Nxd4
{ 13...Nxe5  not possible because  14.f3  followed by Re1 and Black has too many pieces on the e file. }
14. Nxd4
{ After  14.cxd4  a5  , White has no way to avoid a4 by displacing the knight from b3. }
14... c5 15. Nxe6 Qxe6 16. f3
{ If White does not push out this knight now, Black can follow up with ...c4 for Nc5. }
16... Ng5 17. Bxg5
{ This is White's other idea in this position. The different color bishops mean that White can make himself strong on squares of his color by pressing on d5 and f5, but the positions are quite equal and Black must hold with precise play. }
17... Bxg5 18. f4 Be7 19. Qf3
{ The most normal move, preparing the pressure on d5. } 19... c4
{ Black needs to create counterplay on black squares and have ...d4 at hand to simplify the position. }
20. Rfd1 Rad8 21. Rd2 Bc5+ 22. Kh1
{ 22.Kf1  has been tried  but Black can follow the same plan and it does not change the position too much. }
22... Rd7 23. Rad1 Rfd8
{ Black has come to defend d5 and has the ...d4 break to simplify the position. }
24. h3 { White looks for the other weakness. } 24... g6
{ Holding f5 and giving space to the king before breaking with ...d4. } 25. g4
fxg4 26. hxg4 d4
{ Changes are unavoidable and the position is approaching the draws. } 27. cxd4
Rxd4 28. Rxd4 Rxd4 29. Rxd4 Bxd4 30. Qa8+
{ Checks don't scare too much since Black has everything defended. } 30... Kg7
31. Qb7+ Kh8 32. Qb8+ Kg7 33. Qc7+ Qf7
{ Now  33...Kh8  was not possible because of  34.Qd8+  and Qxd4. A draw is inevitable. }
*

